	<p class="cs709C557D"><span class="cs5E1DB61D">WEST virginia legislature</span></p><p class="cs1CE9D70E"><span class="csB0C9F1E0">2026 regular session</span></p><p class="cs709C557D"><span class="csC2FEE544">Committee Substitute</span></p><p class="cs709C557D"><span class="csC2FEE544">for</span></p><p class="cs3E63B65"><span class="cs8498B7A6">Senate Bill 939</span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="csADC6E5DB">By Senator Jeffries</span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="cs7B75DFFE">[Reported </span><span class="cs21863F5F">January 14, 2026</span><span class="cs7B75DFFE">, from the Committee on </span><span class="cs21863F5F">Enter Committee</span><span class="cs7B75DFFE">]</span></p><p class="cs709C557D"><span class="cs5E1DB61D">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs709C557D"><span class="cs5E1DB61D">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs29F66C3F"><span class="csEF05ACC">A BILL to amend the Code of West Virginia, 1931, as amended, by adding a new article, designated &sect;11-13NN-1, &sect;11-13NN-2, &sect;11-13NN-3, &sect;11-13NN-4, &sect;11-13NN-5, &sect;11-13NN-6, &sect;11-13NN-7, &sect;11-13NN-8, &sect;11-13NN-9, &sect;11-13NN-10, &sect;11-13NN-11, &sect;11-13NN-12, &sect;11-13NN-13, and &sect;11-13NN-14, all relating to taxation; creating West Virginia Reshoring Manufacturing Act; providing legislative findings; defining terms; creating the reshoring tax credit; providing for the amount of the credit; establishing requirements for credit; providing eligibility and certification requirements; ; providing for application of credit against state taxes; providing for application, use, forfeiture, and accountability of the credit; providing for limited carryforward and carryback; providing for rulemaking; establishing burden of proof for tax credit; providing for sunset of Act unless reauthorized by Legislature; eliminating new credits after sunset; preserving credits earned prior to sunset; and providing an effective date.</span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Be it enacted by the Legislature of West Virginia:</span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">&nbsp;</span></p><h2 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="cs456817A0">ARTICLE 13NN. WEST Virginia reshoring Manufacturing act.</span></h2>
	<h4 class="cs63FD752D">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;11-13NN-1. Short title.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">This article may be cited as the &quot;West Virginia Reshoring Manufacturing Act&quot;.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;11-13NN-2. Legislative purpose, findings, and intent.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) </span><span class="cs1489E706">Purpose</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">. &mdash; The purpose of this article is to encourage West Virginia businesses to replace foreign-manufactured goods with goods manufactured in West Virginia through performance-based, time-limited tax incentives that support sustained in-state production, workforce expansion, and long-term economic growth.</span></p><p class="cs9A0FB74B"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) </span><span class="cs1489E706">Findings</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">. &mdash; The Legislature finds that:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) According to United States Cens</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">us Bureau foreign trade statistics, businesses operating in West Virginia imported approximately $4.8 billion in foreign manufactured goods during calendar year 2024;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) The $4.8 billion figure reflects only goods formally recorded as imports and does not include foreign-manufactured products purchased by West Virginia busine</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">sses through domestic distributors, wholesalers, resellers, or other domestic supply channels;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) Continued reliance on imported goods exports economic value, employment opportunity, industrial capacity, and taxable activity from this state.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(4) A portion of the imported goods purchased by West Virginia businesses could be competitively manufactured in this state and such state-based manufacturing would increase opportunity for qualified West Virginia manufacturers and will support sustained in-state production, workforce expansion, and long-term economic growth.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(c) </span><span class="cs1489E706">Intent</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">. &mdash; Based on the foregoing, it is the intent of the Legislature to incentivize replacement of imported goods with goods manufactured in West Virginia.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;11-13NN-3. Definitions.</span></h4>
	<h4 class="cs7F45F1B">
		<span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp;</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) &ldquo;Baseline import value&rdquo; means the average annual import transaction value of substantially similar goods imported by the eligible taxpayer during the taxable year immediately preceding the taxable year in which reshoring activity occurs;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) &ldquo;Division&rdquo; means Division of Economic Development;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(c) &quot;Eligible taxpayer&quot; means any person, corporation, partnership, limited liability company, or other business entity subject to taxation under this chapter that purchases goods for resale, distribution, or use in business operations in West Virginia;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(d) &ldquo;Import transaction value&rdquo; means the transaction value declared to United States Customs and Border Protection at the time the imported goods were entered for consumption pursuant to 19 U.S.C. &sect; 1401a, as reflected on Customs Form 7501 or successor documentation;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(e) &quot;Imported goods&quot; means tangible personal property manufactured outside the United States and entered for consumption under federal customs law;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(f) &quot;Qualified West Virginia manufacturer&quot; means a business entity that maintains a physical manufacturing facility in West Virginia and manufactures tangible personal property within the state with such manufacturing constituting the primary production of the reshored product(s) at the in-state facility;</span></p><p class="cs9A0FB74B"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(g) &quot;Reshoring activity&quot; means the documented replacement of imported goods with similar goods manufactured by a qualified West Virginia manufacturer;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(h) &quot;Reshoring activity verification report&quot; means a report prepared by an independent certified public accountant, utilizing agreed-upon procedures, as that term is used under applicable professional auditing standards, prescribed by the </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">division </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">in accordance with generally accepted auditing standards in the United States. The certified public accountant will render a report as to the qualification of the credits, consistent with guidelines to be determined by the </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">division</span><span class="cs46AE26E6"> and approved by the Tax Commissioner;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(i) &ldquo;Substantially similar goods&rdquo; means goods that share the same or comparable Harmonized Tariff Schedule classification at the six-digit level and are commercially interchangeable in use, function, and material composition;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(j) &ldquo;Verified continued reshored activity value&rdquo; means the annual dollar value of repeat purchases of West Virginia-manufactured goods that previously replaced imported goods, as certified pursuant to this article; and</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(k) &ldquo;Verified initial reshoring value&rdquo; means the lesser of:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) The baseline import value of substantially similar goods; or</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) The annual dollar value of purchases from a qualified West Virginia manufacturer replacing those imported goods, as certified pursuant to this article.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;11-13NN-4. Creation of the reshoring tax credit.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) An eligible taxpayer may apply for, and the Tax Commissioner shall allow a nonrefundable tax credit in an amount equal to the percentage specified in &sect;11-13NN-5 of this code of:</span></p><p class="cs9A0FB74B"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Verified initial reshoring value; and</span></p><p class="cs9A0FB74B"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Verified continued reshored activity value. </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) Expenditures utilized by an eligible taxpayer for purposes of calculating the tax credit authorized by this article shall in no event be utilized by the eligible taxpayer for the purpose of calculating or qualifying investment for claiming the economic opportunity tax credit authorized by &sect;11-13Q-1 </span><span class="cs1489E706">et seq</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">. of this code or the manufacturing investment tax credit authorized by &sect;11-13S-1 </span><span class="cs1489E706">et seq</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">. of this code.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;11-13NN-5. Amount of credit allowed; limitation of the credits.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp;	</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) </span><span class="cs1489E706">Base allowance</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">. &mdash; The amount of credit allowed to every eligible taxpayer, except as provided in subsection (b) of this section, is </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">25 percent of verified initial reshoring value.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) </span><span class="cs1489E706">Repeat allowance for continued reshored activity purchases. </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">&mdash; The amount of credit allowed to every eligible taxpayer for </span><span class="cs1489E706">continued</span><span class="cs1489E706"> reshored activity purchases</span><span class="cs46AE26E6"> is:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Twenty percent of verified continued reshored activity value in the second taxable year;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Fifteen percent of verified continued reshored activity value in the third taxable year;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) Ten percent of verified continued reshored activity value in the fourth taxable year; and </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(4) Five percent of verified continued reshored activity value in the fifth taxable year.</span></p><p class="cs9A0FB74B"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(c) </span><span class="cs1489E706">Annual limitation</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">. &mdash; The total tax credit authorized for any eligible taxpayer, including any carry over or carry back, may not ex</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">ceed $1 million </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">within a taxable year.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(d) </span><span class="cs1489E706">Application of the credits</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">. &mdash; The tax credit allowed under this section shall be applied to the eligible taxpayer&rsquo;s state tax liability as provided in &sect;11-13NN-7 of this code.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;11-13NN-6. Requirements for credit.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) The </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">division </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">shall determine the eligibility of the taxpayer, the qualification of the reshoring activity, whether involving initial reshoring or continued reshored activity or both, and the qualification of the West Virginia manufacturer. The </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">division</span><span class="cs46AE26E6"> shall report this information to the Tax Commissioner in a manner and at times the </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">division </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">and the Tax Commissioner shall agree upon. In order for any eligible taxpayer to claim a tax credit under this article, it shall comply with the following requirements:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Apply to the </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">division </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">for the reshoring tax credit on forms and in the manner the </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">division </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">may prescribe; </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Submit information required by the </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">division </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">to demonstrate conformity with the requirements of this section and shall agree in writing:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(A) To pay all obligations the eligible taxpayer has incurred in West Virginia; and</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(B) To delay filing of a claim for the tax credit authorized by this article until the </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">division </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">delivers written notification to the Tax Commissioner that the eligible taxpayer has fulfilled all requirements for the credit.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) Upon completion of the reshoring activity, whether involving initial reshoring activity or continued reshored activity or both, and prior to applying for the reshoring tax credit:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) An eligible taxpayer shall have filed all required West Virginia tax reports and returns and paid any balance of West Virginia tax due on those returns; and</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) All claims for the tax credit shall be filed with a reshoring activity verification report.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(c) If the requirements of this section have been complied with, the </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">division </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">shall approve the reshoring activity tax credit and issue a document granting the appropriate tax credit to the eligible taxpayer and shall report this information to the Tax Commissioner.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(d) Valuation certification. &mdash; The reshoring activity verification report required by this section shall:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Confirm the import transaction value using official customs entry documentation;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Establish the baseline import value based on the immediately preceding taxable year;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) Confirm that purchases from the qualified West Virginia manufacturer are commercially comparable to the replaced imports; and</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(4) Certify that the claimed verified initial reshoring value does not exceed the documented baseline import value.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;11-13NN-7. Application of credit to state taxes.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) </span><span class="cs1489E706">Credit allowed</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">. &ndash;- Beginning in the taxable year that </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">verified initial reshoring activity or verified continued reshored activity occurs</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">, eligible taxpayers and owners of eligible taxpayers are permitted a credit, as described in </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">&sect;11-13NN-5 of this code</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">, against the taxes imposed by &sect;11-24-1 </span><span class="cs1489E706">et seq.</span><span class="cs46AE26E6"> and &sect;11-21-1 </span><span class="cs1489E706">et seq.</span><span class="cs46AE26E6"> of this code, in that order, as specified in this section.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) </span><span class="cs1489E706">Corporation net income taxes</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">. -&ndash; After application of subsection (a) of this section, any unused credit is next applied to reduce the taxes imposed by </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">&sect;11-24-1 </span><span class="cs1489E706">et seq. </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">of this code </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">for the taxable year, determined before application of allowable credits against tax.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(c) </span><span class="cs1489E706">Personal income tax</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">. &ndash; </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) If the eligible taxpayer is an electing small business corporation (as defined in Section 1361 of the United States Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as amended), a partnership, a limited liability company that is treated as a partnership for federal income tax purposes or a sole proprietorship, then any unused credit, after application of subsections (a) and (b) of this subsection, is allowed as a credit against the taxes imposed by </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">&sect;11-21-1 </span><span class="cs1489E706">et seq.</span><span class="cs46AE26E6"> of this code on the income from business or other activity subject to tax under &sect;11-23-1 </span><span class="cs1489E706">et seq.</span><span class="cs46AE26E6"> of this code or on income of a sole proprietor attributable to the business.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Electing small business corporations, limited liability companies, partnerships, and other unincorporated organizations shall allocate the credit allowed by this article among its members in the same manner as profits and losses are allocated for the taxable year.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;11-13NN-8. Uses of credit; unused credit; </span><span class="csF3C8A5A3">limited carry forward </span><span class="csF3C8A5A3">and carry back; </span><span class="csF3C8A5A3">expiration and forfeiture of credit</span><span class="csF3C8A5A3">.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) No credit is allowed under this section against any employer withholding taxes imposed by &sect;11-21-1 </span><span class="cs1489E706">et seq.</span><span class="cs46AE26E6"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">or &sect;11-24-1 </span><span class="cs1489E706">et seq.</span><span class="cs46AE26E6"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">of this code.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) If the tax credit allowed under this article in any taxable year exceeds the sum of the taxes enumerated in &sect;11-13NN-7</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) and &sect;11-13NN-7(c) </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">of this code for that taxable year, the excess may be applied against those taxes, in the order and manner stated in &sect;11-13NN-7 of this code, for </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">one</span><span class="cs46AE26E6"> succeeding taxable year.</span><span class="csF613BC35"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">Thereafter, any remaining tax credit is forfeited.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(c) No carryback is allowed to a prior taxable year that does not have qualified </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">reshoring activity </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">for the amount of any unused portion of any annual credit allowance.</span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;11-13NN-9. Legislative rules.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) The Tax Commissioner </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">and the division </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">shall propose </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">rules for legislative approval in accordance with the provisions of &sect;29A-3-1 </span><span class="cs1489E706">et seq</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">. of this code to implement this article.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) The Tax Commissioner and division shall promulgate emergency rules pursuant to the provisions of &sect;29A-3-15 of this code to implement this article.</span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;11-13NN-10. Burden of proof.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">The burden of proof is on the eligible taxpayer claiming the credit allowed by this article to establish by clear and convincing evidence that the eligible taxpayer or credit transferee is entitled to the amount of credit asserted for the taxable year.</span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;11-13NN-11. Sunset.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">This article shall expire on December 31, </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">2031</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">, unless reauthorized by the Legislature.</span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;11-13NN-12. Elimination of reshoring tax credits after sunset.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">No credit may be earned or certified under this article for reshoring activity occurring after December 31, </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">2031</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">.</span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;11-13NN-13. Preservation of credits earned prior to sunset.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">Any credit earned and certified under this article prior to the sunset date shall remain valid and may be claimed in accordance with this article.</span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;11-13NN-14. Effective date.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">This article shall take effect July 1, 2026, and shall apply to taxable years 2026 through 2031</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">.</span></p>


